subject: Alpine Skiing
lead_paragraph: Lauren Ross rallied in her second run to beat Laurenne Ross (not related) in the women’s giant slalom as the United States Alpine Championships ended in a steady snowfall at Sugarloaf in Carrabassett Valley, Me. Lauren Ross had been fifth after the first run but charged through the second to finish in 2 minutes 15.22 seconds for both runs. Laurenne Ross was second with a combined time of 2:15.31.
